# Reclassify the internal eMMC (mmcblk1) from an SD/MMC card to a fixed hard disk.
#
# KDE Solid/UDisks2 derive the drive type from udev: ID_DRIVE_FLASH_MMC=1 makes the
# eMMC report StorageDrive.driveType=SdMmc. ksystemstats' disk plugin skips SD/MMC
# drives (treating them as removable cards), so it creates NO disk sensors for the
# eMMC and the Plasma System Monitor "Disks" widget shows nothing ("no regular disks").
#
# Clearing the flash-MMC udev flags makes UDisks2/Solid report driveType=HardDisk, so
# ksystemstats enumerates the eMMC and its usage/IO sensors (disk/mmcblk1, disk/<uuid>,
# disk/all) populate. mmcblk1 is the internal eMMC on this device (mmcblk0 is the
# SDIO Wi-Fi); adjust the KERNEL match if your eMMC enumerates differently.
SUBSYSTEM=="block", KERNEL=="mmcblk1", ENV{ID_DRIVE_FLASH_MMC}="", ENV{ID_DRIVE_MEDIA_FLASH_MMC}=""
